        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Office of the Jewish Messenger</placeName>,</p>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>119 West Houston Street</placeName>,</p>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName>, <date>July 21 1863</date>.</p>
            <p>Rev. &amp; dear Sir,</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">I beg to acknowledge<lb/> the receipt of your note of
                    <date>Friday</date>,<lb/> authorizing me to call a meeting of<lb/> the Executive
                Committee of the Board of<lb/> Delegates, but expressing your inability to<lb/> be
                present.</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">As for my part, I deem<lb/> it advisable that you should
                preside,<lb/> if possible, at the meeting and as<lb/> three or more of the Committee
                are<lb/> out of town &amp; I shall myself leave<lb/> to <sic>morrow</sic> for a
                fortnight's trip, I<lb/> have concluded to adopt your<lb/> alternative and wait
                until the first<lb/> or second week in <date>August</date> to<lb/> summon a meeting.
                I leave it to<lb/> you to name the day.</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Wishing you a</p>
            <pb n="2R"/>
            <p>pleasant trip to <placeName>Washington</placeName>,<lb/> in which father
                    joins<add>?</add>, I am</p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">dear sir,</p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">Very Truly Yours</p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">
                <persName role="author">M. J. Isaacs</persName>
            </p>
            <p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>:</p>
        </body>
